parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transfer case gear can cause the vehicle to lose traction, drift into other lanes, and make it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's front wheels spin constantly
the vehicle drifts into other lanes
the AWD system is not working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure (Clunking, Slipping, and Difficulty Shifting)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, and make it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The transmission clunks or makes a loud noise
the vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the vehicle slips out of gear
the transmission has a hard time going between drive and reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission seal failure can cause the transmission to leak fluid, leading to premature wear and eventual failure, which can cause the vehicle to lose power and control.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
transmission seal failure
difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Cooler Failure (Overheating and Fluid Mixing)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission cooler failure can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and eventual failure, which can cause the vehicle to lose power and control.
symptoms: The transmission overheats
engine coolant mixes with transmission fluid
radiator and transmission failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Central Electrical Module can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to safety issues, such as loss of control, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Instrument panel failure
illumination of warning indicators (ABS
Alternator
Urgent Warning System)
unintended activation of windshield wipers
inability to turn off windshield wipers
corrosion of the CEM.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch or Steering Column Lock Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch or steering column lock module can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, making it difficult or impossible to remove the key, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Key becomes stuck in the ignition
car makes a noise like it continues to run after shutdown
inability to remove the key.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Throttle Control Unit can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to safety issues, such as loss of control, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle would not start
vehicle would not accelerate over 25 miles per hour
replacement of the Engine Throttle Control Unit required.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, hard-shift, or jerk, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
hard-shifts
or jerks
especially during deceleration or when the brake is depressed
and may not exceed a certain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and transmission slippage can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine revs up and the vehicle lurches forward when the brake is depressed
especially when the transmission is in gear
and may only return to normal operation when the transmission is shifted into park and the ignition is turned off.
